notesStmt.note: Ya'akov Kats: inscribed with his name, folio 401r, with a date of 421 (1661).
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: The Pentatuech, provided with vowel-points and accents.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 15; written lines: 15; No masoretic comments. Visible difference between hair side and flesh side of the leaf. Visible ruling with pencil. The first word of each book written in larger characters.

history.provenance: Acquisition: Giuseppe Almanzi (b. 1801, d. 1860), bibliophile; his manuscript no. 46: inscribed (folio [406v]); his library including 322 medieval Hebrew manuscripts were purchased en bloc by the British Museum in October 1865 for £1,000 through Asher & Co., Berlin dealer to the British Museum (see 131-153).
